Class SalesEmployee

  • java.lang.Object
    • domain.Employee
      • domain.SalesEmployee
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Employee>

    public class SalesEmployee
extends Employee
    A class representing a Sales Employee. This class is a child of the class Employee
    Usage example: 
     SalesEmployee myEmployee = new SalesEmployee("Christopher", "Hield", 5000, 50.0, new int[]{5, 6, 7, 8, 9}, 1000, 2000);
 SalesEmployee myEmployee = new SalesEmployee(SalesEmployee otherSalesEmployee);
    Since:
    Version 1.8
    Author:
    Christopher Hield
    See Also:
    Department, Employee, Timecard

    • Field Detail

      • salesAmountNeeded

        private double salesAmountNeeded
        Represents the Sales amount needed by the Sales Employee to earn by commission. If this amount is not met he earns the basic salary.
        See Also:
        getSalesAmountNeeded(), setSalesAmountNeeded(double)

      • weeklySalesTotal

        private double weeklySalesTotal
        Represents the Sales Employee's weekly total sales. This total is useful to determine if the Sales Employee earn by commission.
        See Also:
        getWeeklySalesTotal(), setWeeklySalesTotal(double)

      • SalesEmployee

        public SalesEmployee(java.lang.String fName,
                     java.lang.String lName,
                     int eId,
                     double hRate,
                     int[] daysIn,
                     double salesNeeded,
                     double weeklyTotal)
              throws utils.NullParameterException,
                     utils.BadParameterException
        Constructor for the Sales Employee class - need non-null and non-empty First and Last name, a Sales Employee ID between 1000 and 9999, a higher than zero Hourly Rate, an int Array holding the worked days, sales needed to earn by commission, and a weekly total.
        Parameters:
        fName - The Sales Employee's first name
        lName - The Sales Employee's last name
        eId - The Sales Employee's ID
        hRate - The Sales Employee's Hourly Rate
        daysIn - The Sales Employee's int Array with the worked days
        salesNeeded - The Sales Employee's needed sales to earn by commission
        weeklyTotal - The Sales Employee's weekly total sales
        Throws:
        utils.NullParameterException - If either First name or Last name parameters are Null
        utils.BadParameterException - If either First name or Last name have are longer than 20 characters. If ID is not between 1000 and 9999. If Hourly Rate is less or equal to zero. If Sales Needed or Weekly Total is less or equal to zero
        See Also:
        SalesEmployee(SalesEmployee)

      • getWeeklyPay

        public double getWeeklyPay()
        Returns the Weekly Pay of the Sales Employee. This method overrides the parent method. If the Sales Employee meets the Sales Amount Needed the Weekly Pay is equal to the Weekly Sales Total * BONUS_MULTIPLIER, else it's the Weekly Pay of a regular Employee.
        Overrides:
        getWeeklyPay in class Employee
        Returns:
        Returns the Sales Employee Weekly Pay
        See Also:
        Employee
